txt.en: From the edge of Skrithûrz-ulíma, you hear a noisy Orc called Raulik. His words are delivered directly from Mordor, and he calls for the Orcs of Moria to join Sauron, and serve the Eye.
From the edge of Skrithûrz-ulíma, you hear a noisy Orc called Raulik. His words are delivered directly from Mordor, and he calls for the Orcs of Moria to join Sauron, and serve the Eye.

Raulik is on the outskirts of Skrithûrz-ulíma, a Moria Orc encampment to the north-west of the Orc-watch.\n\nAn Orc of Mordor has disguised himself as a Moria Orc and is encouraging Orcs of Moria to join the Great Eye.
You have defeated Raulik, and stopped the spread of Sauron's influence in this particular passage of Moria.

You have defeated Raulik, and stopped the spread of Sauron's influence in this particular passage of Moria.
'We cannot afford to have the Orcs of Moria frightened into submission to Mordor's power. Raulik must be slain. Seek out Skrithûrz-ulíma, to the north-west.'
Defeat Raulik, the servant of Mordor
